==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polyandry
<hw>Pol`y*an"dry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets>
+ Gr. <grk>'anh`r</grk>, <grk>'andro`s</grk>, man, male: cf. F.
<ets>polyandrie</ets>.]</ety> <def>The possession by a woman of more
than one husband at the same time; -- contrasted with
<ant>monandry</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In law, this falls under the head of
polygamy.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyanthus</ent>⟦br⟧
